ODM will disqualify aspirants who perpetrate violence during campaigns and elections.Deputy director of elections Bob Njagi said the party realised that some aspirants use violence for mileage.&ldquo;Let aspirants who want to fly the ODM flag in the coming elections be careful about violence,&rdquo; he said.Njagi spoke in Kasipul on Wednesday during voter registration. More than 300 youths applied for ID cards and 70 acquired voters&rsquo; cards.He warned that political violence is likely to deter many Kenyans from electing qualified leaders, and it may cause voter apathy among supporters.Njagi assured aspirants of free and fair nominations, as ODM has cleaned its elections board.